comments.comment: @44:50 I really want to believe Bob, but his general lack of details on basically everything is unnerving. Most everything he says is something that can be thought up with a creative mind after watching star wars, which had just come out a few years prior to when he says this took place. Elements on the periodic table are setup that way for a reason based on properties and doesn't prove too much. For example at this timestamped moment. He describes the moment as it should be and how it could be envisioned, but sounds like it's not been lived. He never mentions, "I" walked underneath the craft or it moved above "me" and it disappeared from my point of view from the gravity influence. This is your first time seeing it hover around, and you act like that's supposed to be known that it disappears when its above you. Like you spent hours there everyday working on a project for 6 months and don't have exact dimensions measured of everything? You "estimated" the craft to be roughly 52 feet in diameter that you were working on for 6 months? Doesn't 52 feet in diameter seem a little big for something that holds three, 3 foot tall creatures with a basketball sized power source. He fails to mention much of any details from the briefings he had read before working on the craft when asked about them multiple times. What tests were made on every inch of the ship? What chemicals did you test on the outer shell? Did any acids effect it? Would the material heat up or change colors if you took a blow torch right against it? There was a bullet hole through one so how strong can it be? You guys didn't try to pound on it with a hammer? There's no buttons or anything at all in the craft but this other group is working on the craft and made the dash go transparent somehow and you didn't try to figure out where the button is?  It honestly sounds like something out of a very vivid dream someone may have, being able to easily recall and never forget the experience, but lacking detailed information and only remembering the main points. That being said I still believe we are probably in possession of otherworldly craft. If we had these craft for that long though and have been reverse engineering them. Im curious as to an example of technology that could have stemmed from studying these craft over all these years that might be widely used for different purposes today? But If I properly went through the process of a degree and putting effort in to become a physicist, my title on a google search would not read "self proclaimed physicist".
